12 "CHAPTER 11
13 30-11-1.
14 As used in this chapter, the term:
15 (1) 'Customer' means an individual who is lawfully on the premises of a retail
16 establishment.
17 (2) 'Eligible medical condition' means Crohn's disease, ulcerative colitis, any other
18 inflammatory bowel disease, irritable bowel syndrome, or any other medical condition
19 that requires immediate access to a toilet facility or that requires use of an ostomy device.
20 (3) 'Healthcare provider' means a licensed physician, physician assistant, or nurse
21 practitioner.
22 (4) 'Ostomy device' means a medical device that creates an artificial passage for the
23 elimination of body waste.
24 (5) 'Retail establishment' means a place of business open to the general public for the
25 sale of goods or services.
26 30-11-2.
27 (a) Any retail establishment that has a toilet facility for employee use, which typically does
28 not permit customer access to such employee toilet facility, shall allow a customer to use
29 such toilet facility during normal business hours if the toilet facility is maintained in a
30 reasonably safe manner and all of the following conditions are met:
31 (1) The customer requesting access to the employee toilet facility presents a copy of a
32 written statement, signed and issued by a healthcare provider on such provider's
33 letterhead or of a facility with which the healthcare provider is associated that indicates
34 the customer suffers from an eligible medical condition;
35 (2) A public restroom is not immediately accessible to the customer;
