36 (3) At the time the request for access to the employee toilet facility is made, three or
37 more employees of the retail establishment are working; and
38 (4) The employee toilet facility is located in an area of the retail establishment where
39 providing access would not create an obvious risk to the health or safety of the customer
40 or an obvious security risk to the retail establishment.
41 (b) This Code section shall not apply to a retail establishment that:
42 (1) Sells prescription drugs, if the employee toilet facility is located in an area in which
43 the customer might gain access to any pharmaceuticals; and
44 (2) Maintains records or information that is subject to the federal Health Insurance
45 Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, P.L. 104-191, if the employee toilet facility
46 is located in an area in which such records or information might be accessed.
47 30-11-3.
48 (a) A retail establishment or an employee of a retail establishment shall not be liable for
49 any acts or omissions in allowing a customer access to an employee toilet facility pursuant
50 to the provisions of this chapter, if such acts and omissions meet all of the following:
51 (1) Do not constitute gross, willful, or wanton negligence on the part of the retail
52 establishment or employee of the retail establishment;
53 (2) Occurred in an area of the retail establishment that is not otherwise accessible to
54 customers; and
55 (3) Resulted in injury to or death of the customer or an individual other than an employee
56 accompanying the customer to the employee toilet facility.
57 (b) No retail establishment shall be required to make any physical change to an employee
58 toilet facility to effectuate the purposes of this chapter.
59 30-11-4.
60 Any person who violates this chapter shall be guilty of a misdemeanor."
